                    <h2 class=3D"text question" style=3D"font-size:medium; =
font-style:italic" id=3D"lesson">When would I use the Quadratic Formula?</h=
2>
                    <p class=3D"text">You can use the Quadratic Formula any=
 time you're trying to solve a quadratic equation =E2=80=94 as long as that=
 equation is in the form "(a quadratic expression) that is set equal to zer=
o".</p>
                    <p class=3D"text">Often, the simplest way to solve "<sp=
an class=3D"math"><em>ax</em><sup>2</sup> + <em>bx</em> + <em>c</em> =3D 0<=
/span>" for the value of <span class=3D"math"><em>x</em></span> is to <a hr=
ef=3D"https://www.purplemath.com/modules/factquad.htm">factor the quadratic=
</a>, set each factor equal to zero, and then solve each factor. But someti=
mes the quadratic is too messy, or it doesn't factor at all, or, heck, mayb=
e you just don't feel like factoring. While factoring is not always going t=
o be successful, the Quadratic Formula can always find the answers for you.=
</p>

