                <p class=3D"text">The Quadratic Formula uses the "<span cla=
ss=3D"math"><em>a</em></span>", "<span class=3D"math"><em>b</em></span>", a=
nd "<span class=3D"math"><em>c</em></span>" from "<span class=3D"math"><em>=
ax</em><sup>2</sup> + <em>bx</em> + <em>c</em></span>", where "<span class=
=3D"math"><em>a</em></span>", "<span class=3D"math"><em>b</em></span>", and=
 "<span class=3D"math"><em>c</em></span>" are just numbers; they are the "n=
umerical coefficients" of the quadratic equation they've given you to solve=
.</p>
                <p class=3D"text">The Quadratic Formula is <a href=3D"https=
://www.purplemath.com/modules/sqrquad2.htm#formula">derived</a> from the pr=
ocess of completing the square, and is formally stated as:</p>
                <div id=3D"quadform" style=3D"border-style:solid; border-ra=
dius:15px; border-width:1px; border-color:purple; padding:10px;">
                  <h2 class=3D"text question" style=3D"font-size:medium; fo=
nt-style:italic;">What is the Quadratic Formula?</h2>
                  <p class=3D"text">The Quadratic Formula is a rule that sa=
ys that, in any equation of the form <span class=3D"math"><em>ax</em><sup>2=
