                <p class=3D"text">For this particular quadratic equation, f=
actoring would probably be the faster method. But the Quadratic Formula is =
a plug-n-chug method that will <em>always</em> work. Having "brain freeze" =
on a test and can't factor worth a darn? Use the plug-n-chug Formula; it'll=
 always take care of you!</p>
